**help**
Hi, I'm reading excel file and at the same time I have to validate my rows and heads to my business logic. 
I have an *AnalysisEventListener* for my Data class and I call my validation methods here
```java
public class ProductImportDataExcelListener  extends AnalysisEventListener<ProductImportData> {
    List<ProductImportData> rows = new ArrayList<>();

  @Override
    public void invokeHeadMap( Map<Integer, String> headMap, AnalysisContext context ){
        super.invokeHeadMap(headMap, context);
        validateHead(headMap);
    }

    @Override
    public void invoke( ProductImportData data, AnalysisContext context ) {
       validateRow(data);
    }

   @Override
    public void doAfterAllAnalysed( AnalysisContext context ) {
        System.out.println("Done. Row size " + rows.size());
    }
}
```
I have custom business Exception for my validation logic and I throw an exception and *ExcelAnalysisException* overwrites my custom Exception and listener *stop working*.
Is there any way to ignore this ?

comments.body:
you can try :
```java
   try{
        }catch (ExcelAnalysisException e){
            // This is your exception
           throw e.getCause();
        }
```

If you don't want to break the current code
```java
    @Override
    public void invoke(ProductImportData data, AnalysisContext context) {
        try {
            validateRow(data);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            //TODO exception
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
```
If you only want rollback
```java
    @Override
    public void onException(Exception exception, AnalysisContext context) throws Exception {
        //TODO something before rollback, before super
        super.onException(exception, context);
    }
```
If you want to check the data before the specific logic, it seems to read the data check first, and the second read to execute the specific logic.

I solved as follow;
```java
public class AppError {

    Integer status = 400;
    String title="Bad Request";
    String detail;
     Instant instant = Instant.now();
    List<String> errorDetails = new ArrayList<>();
    String message;
}
// in My controller
 @ExceptionHandler({ExcelAnalysisException.class})
    @ResponseBody
    @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST)
    public ResponseEntity<AppError> handle(Exception e){
        AppError error = new AppError();
        error.setDetail(e.getMessage());
        error.setMessage(e.getMessage());
        return new ResponseEntity<AppError>(error, HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST);
    }
```
It works for me thank you all. :)

Well done! dont forget close issuse.
```
    @ExceptionHandler({ExcelAnalysisException.class})
    @ResponseBody
    @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST)
    public ResponseEntity<AppError> handle(Exception e) {
        //this is what you throw
        final Throwable cause = e.getCause();
        
        AppError error = new AppError();
        error.setDetail(e.getMessage());
        error.setMessage(e.getMessage());
        return new ResponseEntity<AppError>(error, HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST);
    }
```

