EasyExcel uses CGLIB to convert beans to map data types during write operations. CGLIB eventually calls the `java.beans.Introspector#decapitalize` method, which has its own parsing rules. This can cause properties like 'A' to be converted to 'a' through reflection, leading to data mismatches. You can either rename the property or convert it to lowercase to resolve the issue.I strongly recommend using standard camelCase for property names. 

